&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Clinical Fellow in Anaesthetics&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fixed Term 12 Months&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time - 40 hours&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary - £49,036 + Allowances and Weighting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To start - ASAP&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are inviting applications for Senior Clinical Fellows in Anaesthetics to start asap. There are 4 posts available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Post holders will be expected to cover on call duties at either the St Helier Hospital site or Epsom Hospital site on a 1:8 basis.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Anaesthetic Dept of Epsom and St Helier University Hospitals NHS Trust covers a wide variety of elective, day case and emergency surgery on two main sites. We currently cover one Intensive Care Unit and one High Dependency Unit, two Obstetric Units and provide elective anaesthesia on both sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary - £49,036 + Allowances and Weighting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Paul Bathke&lt;br /&gt;Email address - paul.bathke@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
